cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.MA 

The paper discusses a novel approach for wireless communication between different technologies, specifically Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, and ZigBee. This involves the use of backscatter communication, which is a technique commonly used in information theory and wireless communication (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the potential for Internet connectivity for implanted devices (cs.NI) and presents proof-of-concepts for previously infeasible applications, such as a contact lens form-factor antenna prototype and an implantable neural recording interface (cs.EM, cs.AR). Finally, the paper involves the use of hardware prototypes and experimentation (cs.MA).
